The documents clearly indicate that J. M. E. McTaggart was heavily influenced by Hegel, as he produced a large body of Hegel scholarship, including "Studies in Hegelian Cosmology" (1901) and later developed his own metaphysical system in "The Nature of Existence" (1921 & posthumously 1927), which was based on what McTaggart took to be Hegel's ontology.
